The paper deals with the acceptance probability of Moore-Crutchfield Measure Once Quantum Finite Automata (MO-QFA), which is a topic in the intersection of quantum computing and automata theory. Therefore, cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves undecidability results, which suggests that cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with quantum computing, which suggests that cs.QA (Quantum Algebra) is a possible sub-category.
